So these guys are
one in the same.

00:25:55.050 --> 00:25:56.855 align:middle line:90%
They rape and pillage.

00:25:56.855 --> 00:25:58.510 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: This is
a global cartel.

00:25:58.510 --> 00:26:00.390 align:middle line:84%
>>HOFFMAN: Yes, it
is a global cartel.

00:26:00.390 --> 00:26:06.050 align:middle line:84%
And so it's not sim-- it's
not just about gold or about

00:26:06.050 --> 00:26:06.950 align:middle line:90%
stocks.

00:26:06.950 --> 00:26:09.860 align:middle line:84%
It's about basically
taking everything from you

00:26:09.860 --> 00:26:13.190 align:middle line:84%
so that, you know, you
beg people like Obama

00:26:13.190 --> 00:26:16.430 align:middle line:84%
to give you Obamacare,
which has to be

00:26:16.430 --> 00:26:17.719 align:middle line:90%
funded by more printed money.

00:26:17.719 --> 00:26:19.510 align:middle line:84%
See that's where the
Ponzi scheme comes in.

00:26:19.510 --> 00:26:21.650 align:middle line:84%
That's their weakness,
is the paper money.

00:26:21.650 --> 00:26:24.120 align:middle line:90%
You can't print it forever.

00:26:24.120 --> 00:26:25.200 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Well, why not?

00:26:25.200 --> 00:26:27.240 align:middle line:90%
They've been doing it for years.

00:26:27.240 --> 00:26:30.380 align:middle line:84%
I mean, that's what people
keep saying is, looks OK to me.

00:26:30.380 --> 00:26:31.720 align:middle line:90%
I haven't lost my job yet.

00:26:31.720 --> 00:26:33.292 align:middle line:84%
Of course, your
mother has moved back

00:26:33.292 --> 00:26:34.500 align:middle line:90%
in because she lost her home.

00:26:34.500 --> 00:26:37.510 align:middle line:84%
Your kids move back in because
they can't find any work.

00:26:37.510 --> 00:26:39.030 align:middle line:90%
But still it looks normal.

00:26:39.030 --> 00:26:41.827 align:middle line:84%
You still have some things
on the shelves at Walmart.

00:26:41.827 --> 00:26:44.160 align:middle line:84%
>>HOFFMAN: Well, you-- and I
don't mean you personally--

00:26:44.160 --> 00:26:45.902 align:middle line:90%
but you may still have your job.

00:26:45.902 --> 00:26:47.860 align:middle line:84%
But the real unemployment
rate in this country,

00:26:47.860 --> 00:26:49.490 align:middle line:84%
and I'm talking
about the real rate,

00:26:49.490 --> 00:26:52.590 align:middle line:84%
meaning people who can't
afford to pay their bills,

00:26:52.590 --> 00:26:54.460 align:middle line:90%
is closer to 20, 25%.

00:26:54.460 --> 00:26:56.250 align:middle line:84%
And it's only
going to get worse.

00:26:56.250 --> 00:26:58.460 align:middle line:84%
And yes, they can
keep printing money.

00:26:58.460 --> 00:26:59.340 align:middle line:90%
They have.

00:26:59.340 --> 00:27:02.450 align:middle line:84%
But in terms of the government
statistics, the CPI,

00:27:02.450 --> 00:27:04.960 align:middle line:84%
the Consumer Price Index,
that's their statistics which

00:27:04.960 --> 00:27:07.330 align:middle line:84%
are heavily
understated, the dollar

00:27:07.330 --> 00:27:09.770 align:middle line:84%
has lost 98% of its
purchasing power

00:27:09.770 --> 00:27:11.670 align:middle line:84%
since the Federal
Reserve was created.

00:27:11.670 --> 00:27:15.950 align:middle line:84%
It's lost 50% since we went
off the gold standard in 1970.

00:27:15.950 --> 00:27:17.424 align:middle line:84%
And that's just
what they tell you.

00:27:17.424 --> 00:27:19.340 align:middle line:84%
They tell you we printed
this amount of money.

00:27:19.340 --> 00:27:20.690 align:middle line:90%
You know they've printed more.

00:27:20.690 --> 00:27:22.140 align:middle line:84%
They tell you this is
the inflation rate.

00:27:22.140 --> 00:27:22.990 align:middle line:90%
You know it's more.

00:27:22.990 --> 00:27:26.270 align:middle line:84%
Just like they tell you we
have 8,133 tons of gold,

00:27:26.270 --> 00:27:29.020 align:middle line:84%
which anyone in my
world knows they don't.

00:27:29.020 --> 00:27:30.470 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Where'd it go?

00:27:30.470 --> 00:27:32.830 align:middle line:84%
>>HOFFMAN: They leased
it and sold it secretly

00:27:32.830 --> 00:27:34.800 align:middle line:84%
to maintain the
value of the dollar.

00:27:34.800 --> 00:27:36.780 align:middle line:90%
That's their Achilles heel.

00:27:36.780 --> 00:27:38.440 align:middle line:84%
Because gold and
silver are real money.

00:27:38.440 --> 00:27:40.450 align:middle line:90%
And they always have been.

00:27:40.450 --> 00:27:43.660 align:middle line:84%
And what I say when people
ask about that, I say look.

00:27:43.660 --> 00:27:47.450 align:middle line:84%
Even if you're the number one--
you're literally Joe six pack,

00:27:47.450 --> 00:27:48.230 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:27:48.230 --> 00:27:49.970 align:middle line:84%
You don't work in the
financial industry.

00:27:49.970 --> 00:27:51.410 align:middle line:90%
You don't have much money.

00:27:51.410 --> 00:27:53.590 align:middle line:84%
You know nothing about
financial markets.

00:27:53.590 --> 00:27:55.530 align:middle line:84%
There's probably
two things that are

00:27:55.530 --> 00:27:57.780 align:middle line:84%
ingrained in your
DNA about markets.

00:27:57.780 --> 00:28:00.780 align:middle line:84%
One is the Dow Jones
Industrial Average,

00:28:00.780 --> 00:28:04.470 align:middle line:84%
which is supposedly a barometer
of the health of the nation,

00:28:04.470 --> 00:28:05.030 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:28:05.030 --> 00:28:06.364 align:middle line:90%
And you also know about gold.

00:28:06.364 --> 00:28:08.280 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: We've been
watching what's happened.

00:28:08.280 --> 00:28:10.350 align:middle line:84%
All of us have been watching
what's happened with gold.

00:28:10.350 --> 00:28:12.141 align:middle line:84%
And a lot of people
have migrated that way,

00:28:12.141 --> 00:28:14.470 align:middle line:84%
have gotten out of the
markets and moved toward gold.

00:28:14.470 --> 00:28:16.820 align:middle line:84%
And it went as high
as, what was it?

00:28:16.820 --> 00:28:18.900 align:middle line:90%
Just under 2,000 a while back.

00:28:18.900 --> 00:28:21.290 align:middle line:90%
And it's back down around 1,600.

00:28:21.290 --> 00:28:24.540 align:middle line:84%
But it's interesting because
just as the world is becoming

00:28:24.540 --> 00:28:27.160 align:middle line:84%
even less stable,
everything's coming unglued.

00:28:27.160 --> 00:28:28.940 align:middle line:84%
Bad news everywhere,
which normally you

00:28:28.940 --> 00:28:30.760 align:middle line:84%
should see the gold
going like that.

00:28:30.760 --> 00:28:32.140 align:middle line:90%
It's not.

00:28:32.140 --> 00:28:33.650 align:middle line:90%
It's not really moving.

00:28:33.650 --> 00:28:37.390 align:middle line:84%
It's been stuck in the same
place for a couple months now.

00:28:37.390 --> 00:28:39.360 align:middle line:90%
What's actually happening?

00:28:39.360 --> 00:28:41.260 align:middle line:84%
Are those fixed
too, those prices

00:28:41.260 --> 00:28:43.820 align:middle line:84%
fixed too-- the gold
market, silver market?

00:28:43.820 --> 00:28:46.270 align:middle line:84%
>>HOFFMAN: Well, first
I'd say that I disagree

00:28:46.270 --> 00:28:47.970 align:middle line:90%
that people are watching gold.

00:28:47.970 --> 00:28:49.600 align:middle line:90%
You may be watching personally.

00:28:49.600 --> 00:28:52.160 align:middle line:10%
And you probably did some
research for the show,

00:28:52.160 --> 00:28:53.960 align:middle line:10%
but from my experience
in the world,

00:28:53.960 --> 00:28:56.180 align:middle line:10%
probably one out of
1,000 people even

00:28:56.180 --> 00:28:58.850 align:middle line:10%
has knowledge that gold is
a market that's tradeable.

00:28:58.850 --> 00:28:59.140 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA: Seriously.

00:28:59.140 --> 00:29:01.140 align:middle line:10%
>>HOFFMAN: Let alone to
understand what it means

00:29:01.140 --> 00:29:03.700 align:middle line:10%
or how to buy it.

00:29:03.700 --> 00:29:07.110 align:middle line:10%
So as far as your second
question, is it manipulated?

00:29:07.110 --> 00:29:09.350 align:middle line:84%
There is no market
more manipulated

00:29:09.350 --> 00:29:10.780 align:middle line:90%
than the precious metals.

00:29:10.780 --> 00:29:12.660 align:middle line:84%
Because as I mentioned
before, they're

00:29:12.660 --> 00:29:14.530 align:middle line:90%
the linchpin of the system.

00:29:14.530 --> 00:29:17.870 align:middle line:84%
They are the barometer
of something being wrong.

00:29:17.870 --> 00:29:22.470 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And so here it's stuck
around 1,600, up or down $20

00:29:22.470 --> 00:29:25.100 align:middle line:84%
as the weeks have
gone on, I've noticed.

00:29:25.100 --> 00:29:28.100 align:middle line:84%
And yet I've read over
the last few years,

00:29:28.100 --> 00:29:30.590 align:middle line:84%
many people I've talked to
on the subject have said,

00:29:30.590 --> 00:29:35.320 align:middle line:84%
realistically, gold should
be over 2,000, 2,500, $3,000.

00:29:35.320 --> 00:29:36.947 align:middle line:84%
In real terms, that
should be where

00:29:36.947 --> 00:29:40.150 align:middle line:90%
it-- that's where it should be.

00:29:40.150 --> 00:29:42.920 align:middle line:10%
>>HOFFMAN: Well, first of all,
again we talked about the Dow

00:29:42.920 --> 00:29:45.710 align:middle line:10%
at 13,000, how everyone's
crowing about it.

00:29:45.710 --> 00:29:49.450 align:middle line:10%
The Dow was 13,000 12 years ago.

00:29:49.450 --> 00:29:52.850 align:middle line:10%
And that's again, that's
the pre-Citigroup Dow.

00:29:52.850 --> 00:29:54.810 align:middle line:10%
And that's not
including inflation.

00:29:54.810 --> 00:29:56.590 align:middle line:10%
Just on an absolute
basis, the Dow

00:29:56.590 --> 00:29:58.070 align:middle line:10%
is the same as it
was 12 years ago.

00:29:58.070 --> 00:30:00.780 align:middle line:10%
But the mainstream media, every
time it goes up 20 points,

00:30:00.780 --> 00:30:02.240 align:middle line:10%
talks about how
great it's doing.

00:30:02.240 --> 00:30:04.110 align:middle line:10%
It hasn't gone anywhere.

00:30:04.110 --> 00:30:06.780 align:middle line:84%
Gold has been up for
12 years in a row.

00:30:06.780 --> 00:30:09.020 align:middle line:84%
Gold was up last year
after they smashed it

00:30:09.020 --> 00:30:10.740 align:middle line:84%
down purposely, the
government, after it

00:30:10.740 --> 00:30:12.520 align:middle line:90%
hit that high in September.

00:30:12.520 --> 00:30:13.870 align:middle line:90%
It was up 13%.

00:30:13.870 --> 00:30:17.700 align:middle line:84%
Gold has been, this year
because the system is getting so

00:30:17.700 --> 00:30:20.420 align:middle line:84%
near the end, and so
frayed, and the currencies

00:30:20.420 --> 00:30:23.010 align:middle line:84%
are being over printed,
and the debt is spiraling,

00:30:23.010 --> 00:30:24.950 align:middle line:84%
I have never seen
in my life anything

00:30:24.950 --> 00:30:27.140 align:middle line:84%
like what we see in the
suppression this year.

00:30:27.140 --> 00:30:29.590 align:middle line:90%
And still, gold is up this year.

00:30:29.590 --> 00:30:33.080 align:middle line:84%
It's very resilient because
underlying the paper that they

00:30:33.080 --> 00:30:35.850 align:middle line:84%
are naked shorting, which means
basically selling things that--

00:30:35.850 --> 00:30:36.610 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Tell us
about shorting.

00:30:36.610 --> 00:30:38.750 align:middle line:84%
A lot of people don't
understand shorting.

00:30:38.750 --> 00:30:39.470 align:middle line:90%
>>HOFFMAN: OK.

00:30:39.470 --> 00:30:41.930 align:middle line:84%
Shorting, if you
go all the way back

00:30:41.930 --> 00:30:45.410 align:middle line:84%
to the '70s when it was created,
maybe even the late '60s when

00:30:45.410 --> 00:30:47.970 align:middle line:84%
it was created, it was
really, once again,

00:30:47.970 --> 00:30:50.420 align:middle line:90%
a banking invention for fees.

00:30:50.420 --> 00:30:54.070 align:middle line:84%
Basically it allows you to
borrow someone else's shares,

00:30:54.070 --> 00:30:59.300 align:middle line:84%
or gold, or bonds, and bet
that they will go down,

00:30:59.300 --> 00:31:02.240 align:middle line:84%
wherein where you'd buy them
back and then return the shares

00:31:02.240 --> 00:31:05.350 align:middle line:84%
and pay the brokerage a
fee for that lending that's

00:31:05.350 --> 00:31:07.520 align:middle line:90%
called margin.

00:31:07.520 --> 00:31:09.910 align:middle line:84%
But as time went
on, people started

00:31:09.910 --> 00:31:12.760 align:middle line:84%
to use shorting in
a more sinister way.

00:31:12.760 --> 00:31:17.370 align:middle line:84%
Once the banks realized
that they can kind of double

00:31:17.370 --> 00:31:20.410 align:middle line:84%
the market, meaning you have
people buying on one side.

00:31:20.410 --> 00:31:23.030 align:middle line:84%
And then you have--
you're creating shares

00:31:23.030 --> 00:31:24.500 align:middle line:84%
on the other side
to sell, you're

00:31:24.500 --> 00:31:26.930 align:middle line:90%
creating more commissions.

00:31:26.930 --> 00:31:29.470 align:middle line:84%
And so they started
to promote it heavily.

00:31:29.470 --> 00:31:31.900 align:middle line:84%
And then, of course, there
became the manipulation.

00:31:31.900 --> 00:31:35.380 align:middle line:84%
Once governments-- once the
US government, in particular,

00:31:35.380 --> 00:31:37.860 align:middle line:84%
realized that they
can naked short,

00:31:37.860 --> 00:31:40.474 align:middle line:84%
which means create
shares and gold, paper--

00:31:40.474 --> 00:31:42.140 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: That don't
exist in real gold.

00:31:42.140 --> 00:31:43.940 align:middle line:84%
>>HOFFMAN: That
don't exist, yeah.

00:31:43.940 --> 00:31:46.180 align:middle line:84%
There are laws that
say you can't do it.

00:31:46.180 --> 00:31:47.180 align:middle line:90%
But that's what they do.

00:31:47.180 --> 00:31:47.605 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yeah, I
was going to say,

00:31:47.605 --> 00:31:49.800 align:middle line:84%
it sounds-- another thing
that sounds illegal to me,

00:31:49.800 --> 00:31:50.700 align:middle line:90%
I mean should be illegal.

00:31:50.700 --> 00:31:52.158 align:middle line:84%
>>HOFFMAN: It's
completely illegal.

00:31:52.158 --> 00:31:54.159 align:middle line:90%
But that's what they do.

00:31:54.159 --> 00:31:55.200 align:middle line:90%
I mean, it's very simple.

00:31:55.200 --> 00:31:58.010 align:middle line:84%
They just put in an order
and say sell paper gold,

00:31:58.010 --> 00:32:01.300 align:middle line:84%
sell stocks, sell gold mining
shares, whatever it is.

00:32:01.300 --> 00:32:02.550 align:middle line:90%
And the market goes down.

00:32:02.550 --> 00:32:04.970 align:middle line:84%
And since the CFTC,
which is the commodities

00:32:04.970 --> 00:32:08.010 align:middle line:84%
regulator, and the SEC,
which is the stock regulator,

00:32:08.010 --> 00:32:11.390 align:middle line:84%
are all part of the same team,
they do whatever they want.

00:32:11.390 --> 00:32:14.620 align:middle line:84%
I'm sure it won't surprise you
that the CFTC, which again,

00:32:14.620 --> 00:32:17.710 align:middle line:84%
they regulate commodities, is
run by a former Goldman Sachs

00:32:17.710 --> 00:32:18.820 align:middle line:90%
executive.

00:32:18.820 --> 00:32:22.780 align:middle line:84%
And the same will go across
all of these agencies, which

00:32:22.780 --> 00:32:25.651 align:middle line:90%
are supposedly regulatory.

00:32:25.651 --> 00:32:26.150 align:middle line:90%
So--

00:32:26.150 --> 00:32:27.000 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: It doesn't
sound like there's

00:32:27.000 --> 00:32:29.207 align:middle line:84%
much regulation of any
kind going on, though.

00:32:29.207 --> 00:32:29.790 align:middle line:90%
>>HOFFMAN: No.

00:32:29.790 --> 00:32:31.710 align:middle line:10%
No, in fact, they
created this thing

00:32:31.710 --> 00:32:34.640 align:middle line:10%
called Dodd-Frank about three
or four years ago, which

00:32:34.640 --> 00:32:38.520 align:middle line:10%
celebrated its second or third
anniversary a week or two ago.

00:32:38.520 --> 00:32:40.380 align:middle line:10%
It hasn't even
been finished yet.

00:32:40.380 --> 00:32:43.211 align:middle line:10%
So they crow about how they're
creating regulation to help.

00:32:43.211 --> 00:32:44.960 align:middle line:10%
But they don't even
finish the regulation.

00:32:44.960 --> 00:32:47.530 align:middle line:10%
I think it's something like
2000 pages and growing.

00:32:47.530 --> 00:32:49.640 align:middle line:10%
But it hasn't
regulated anything.

00:32:49.640 --> 00:32:52.280 align:middle line:84%
And the point is, it's
not going to be regulated.

00:32:52.280 --> 00:32:54.350 align:middle line:84%
The whole point is the
banks and the government

00:32:54.350 --> 00:32:56.940 align:middle line:84%
have now become so
powerful that they realize

00:32:56.940 --> 00:32:58.660 align:middle line:84%
that they don't
have to regulate.

00:32:58.660 --> 00:33:00.870 align:middle line:84%
The average person
doesn't have the money

00:33:00.870 --> 00:33:03.280 align:middle line:84%
to even protect themself,
let alone the will

00:33:03.280 --> 00:33:05.990 align:middle line:84%
to try to figure out the
complexities of derivatives

00:33:05.990 --> 00:33:07.960 align:middle line:84%
and naked shorting
and algorithms,

00:33:07.960 --> 00:33:11.320 align:middle line:84%
which are computer programs that
are used to manipulate markets.

00:33:11.320 --> 00:33:14.594 align:middle line:84%
And it gets to the point where
people just throw in the flag.

00:33:14.594 --> 00:33:17.780 align:middle line:84%
You know, even a few years ago,
they might be looking at the TV

00:33:17.780 --> 00:33:19.457 align:middle line:84%
and saying oh, well
the Dow is going up.

00:33:19.457 --> 00:33:20.540 align:middle line:90%
I guess things are better.

00:33:20.540 --> 00:33:22.420 align:middle line:84%
People don't even look
at the Dow anymore.

00:33:22.420 --> 00:33:25.490 align:middle line:90%
In fact, there's been outflows.

00:33:25.490 --> 00:33:27.640 align:middle line:84%
They have statistics
that measure people's

00:33:27.640 --> 00:33:29.950 align:middle line:84%
inflows and outflows
into mutual funds.

00:33:29.950 --> 00:33:32.840 align:middle line:84%
And they've been net outflow
I think for two straight years

00:33:32.840 --> 00:33:33.920 align:middle line:90%
every single month.

00:33:33.920 --> 00:33:36.170 align:middle line:84%
So when you see
the Dow going up,

00:33:36.170 --> 00:33:39.260 align:middle line:84%
you got to say well,
who's buying it.

00:33:39.260 --> 00:33:40.990 align:middle line:90%
And the same goes with gold.

00:33:40.990 --> 00:33:44.220 align:middle line:84%
You say well, why is it
not going up this year?

00:33:44.220 --> 00:33:47.260 align:middle line:84%
Why does it seem like every
time something wildly bullish

00:33:47.260 --> 00:33:50.870 align:middle line:84%
for gold happens, it just
plummets $20.00 in 10 seconds.

00:33:50.870 --> 00:33:51.390 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:33:51.390 --> 00:33:51.700 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:33:51.700 --> 00:33:53.825 align:middle line:84%
>>HOFFMAN: And it's the
same reason; the government

00:33:53.825 --> 00:33:57.460 align:middle line:84%
is creating paper on one side
to support things that it likes.

00:33:57.460 --> 00:33:59.640 align:middle line:84%
And it's creating
paper on the other side

00:33:59.640 --> 00:34:01.934 align:middle line:84%
to manipulate the price
of things it doesn't like.

00:34:01.934 --> 00:34:03.350 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So what
is the advantage

00:34:03.350 --> 00:34:05.650 align:middle line:84%
of manipulating
the price of gold

00:34:05.650 --> 00:34:08.382 align:middle line:84%
downward and
keeping a lid on it?

00:34:08.382 --> 00:34:10.340 align:middle line:84%
>>HOFFMAN: Because it
keeps it out of the news.

00:34:10.340 --> 00:34:13.929 align:middle line:84%
When people see gold going
up, even the mainstream media

00:34:13.929 --> 00:34:16.800 align:middle line:84%
will be forced to write
inflation expectations,

00:34:16.800 --> 00:34:18.760 align:middle line:90%
inflation fears.

00:34:18.760 --> 00:34:21.520 align:middle line:84%
The government, the Fed's
policies are not working.

00:34:21.520 --> 00:34:23.429 align:middle line:90%
The Fed is supposedly in charge.

00:34:23.429 --> 00:34:25.440 align:middle line:84%
They supposedly
know what's right.

00:34:25.440 --> 00:34:27.520 align:middle line:90%
And so they must keep it down.

00:34:27.520 --> 00:34:30.659 align:middle line:84%
Because there's such a tiny
supply of gold in the world.

00:34:30.659 --> 00:34:34.406 align:middle line:84%
I mean, it's probably only
a couple of trillion dollars

00:34:34.406 --> 00:34:36.750 align:middle line:90%
of gold that's ever been mined.

00:34:36.750 --> 00:34:39.560 align:middle line:84%
Of course, almost all of
it is hidden in vaults

00:34:39.560 --> 00:34:40.909 align:middle line:90%
that you'll never see again.

00:34:40.909 --> 00:34:43.969 align:middle line:84%
As far as silver, there's only
about a billion ounces above

00:34:43.969 --> 00:34:48.000 align:middle line:84%
ground existing, because most of
it's been depleted by industry.

00:34:48.000 --> 00:34:51.219 align:middle line:84%
A billion ounces is
worth $30 billion.

00:34:51.219 --> 00:34:53.510 align:middle line:84%
I think there's 1,200
billionaires in the world.

00:34:53.510 --> 00:34:56.020 align:middle line:84%
And there's probably 10
times as many corporations

00:34:56.020 --> 00:34:59.170 align:middle line:84%
that could take that
supply out, much of which,

00:34:59.170 --> 00:35:01.310 align:middle line:84%
again, is sitting in
vaults, never to be used.

00:35:01.310 --> 00:35:05.265 align:middle line:84%
So it's a very fine line about
the physical supply of gold

00:35:05.265 --> 00:35:07.720 align:middle line:84%
and silver, and the
paper naked shorting

00:35:07.720 --> 00:35:09.140 align:middle line:90%
that tries to hold them down.

00:35:09.140 --> 00:35:10.639 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And let's
talk about that.

00:35:10.639 --> 00:35:12.800 align:middle line:84%
Because now once you
realize the fraud

00:35:12.800 --> 00:35:16.350 align:middle line:84%
that was going on in the world,
including in your own life,

00:35:16.350 --> 00:35:19.570 align:middle line:84%
including among your fellow
employees and your bosses

00:35:19.570 --> 00:35:21.950 align:middle line:84%
and so forth, you decided
to get out of the game.

00:35:21.950 --> 00:35:24.480 align:middle line:84%
And other people I've
interviewed did the same thing.

00:35:24.480 --> 00:35:26.480 align:middle line:84%
And the first
place they went was

00:35:26.480 --> 00:35:29.820 align:middle line:84%
anything-- go to high ground,
go to higher ground, which

00:35:29.820 --> 00:35:32.410 align:middle line:90%
was to gold and silver.

00:35:32.410 --> 00:35:35.120 align:middle line:84%
And so now that's
really what you do.

00:35:35.120 --> 00:35:36.580 align:middle line:84%
That's a big part
of your life is

00:35:36.580 --> 00:35:39.530 align:middle line:84%
gold and silver, and the
marketing of gold and silver.

00:35:39.530 --> 00:35:42.240 align:middle line:84%
So let's just be upfront about
that, and it's for a reason.

00:35:42.240 --> 00:35:44.660 align:middle line:84%
Because that was the only safe
place you could see to go.

00:35:44.660 --> 00:35:45.326 align:middle line:90%
>>HOFFMAN: Yeah.

00:35:45.326 --> 00:35:47.280 align:middle line:84%
Gold and silver is
the highest ground.

00:35:47.280 --> 00:35:48.070 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: The highest
ground, right.

00:35:48.070 --> 00:35:49.370 align:middle line:84%
>>HOFFMAN: I mean, there is
no other ground even close.

00:35:49.370 --> 00:35:51.210 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: And I agree.

00:35:51.210 --> 00:35:54.410 align:middle line:84%
From everything I've seen,
read, and looked into,

00:35:54.410 --> 00:35:57.530 align:middle line:84%
it seems that's a very
clear and true statement.

00:35:57.530 --> 00:36:00.650 align:middle line:84%
So now let's talk about real
gold and its value right

00:36:00.650 --> 00:36:04.240 align:middle line:84%
now, today, as opposed to paper
gold and the manipulated gold

00:36:04.240 --> 00:36:05.110 align:middle line:90%
prices.

00:36:05.110 --> 00:36:07.110 align:middle line:90%
And the same thing with silver.

00:36:07.110 --> 00:36:09.130 align:middle line:84%
>>HOFFMAN: Well, without
being too technical,

00:36:09.130 --> 00:36:11.759 align:middle line:84%
the physical price of
gold-- well, I should say,

00:36:11.759 --> 00:36:13.300 align:middle line:84%
the price that you
see on your screen

00:36:13.300 --> 00:36:15.140 align:middle line:90%
for gold is about $1,600.

00:36:15.140 --> 00:36:18.400 align:middle line:84%
And the price you see on your
screen for silver is about $28

00:36:18.400 --> 00:36:19.320 align:middle line:90%
an ounce.

00:36:19.320 --> 00:36:21.970 align:middle line:84%
Of course, you will pay
premiums in the real world.

00:36:21.970 --> 00:36:23.470 align:middle line:84%
If you want to buy
an ounce of gold,

00:36:23.470 --> 00:36:26.300 align:middle line:84%
it'll probably cost
closer to $1,700 today.

00:36:26.300 --> 00:36:29.400 align:middle line:84%
The premiums for gold and
silver are typically five to 15%

00:36:29.400 --> 00:36:31.660 align:middle line:90%
in normal market conditions.

00:36:31.660 --> 00:36:33.930 align:middle line:84%
But we've seen them
blow out-- in 2008,

00:36:33.930 --> 00:36:37.330 align:middle line:84%
they got as high as almost
100% in the silver market,

00:36:37.330 --> 00:36:40.890 align:middle line:84%
and not quite that high
in gold, but pretty high.

00:36:40.890 --> 00:36:45.530 align:middle line:84%
When people fear it, and when
these manipulations start

00:36:45.530 --> 00:36:48.040 align:middle line:84%
to falter, and people
get fear and start

00:36:48.040 --> 00:36:51.960 align:middle line:84%
to try to buy the physical
from like firms like my firm,

00:36:51.960 --> 00:36:53.670 align:middle line:90%
then the premiums extend.

00:36:53.670 --> 00:36:55.760 align:middle line:84%
And the mints run out
of gold and silver.

00:36:55.760 --> 00:36:59.860 align:middle line:84%
And the delays of when you're
going to get it get larger.

00:36:59.860 --> 00:37:05.110 align:middle line:84%
So again, it's a very fine line
of-- that the manipulators are

00:37:05.110 --> 00:37:05.610 align:middle line:90%
fighting.

00:37:05.610 --> 00:37:10.130 align:middle line:84%
Because when it goes too
high, we run out of supply.

00:37:10.130 --> 00:37:12.510 align:middle line:84%
But when it goes too low,
we do the same thing.

00:37:12.510 --> 00:37:14.718 align:middle line:84%
And that's the beauty of
about gold and silver, which

00:37:14.718 --> 00:37:16.270 align:middle line:84%
shows you why it's
not an investment.

00:37:16.270 --> 00:37:17.460 align:middle line:90%
But it's money.

00:37:17.460 --> 00:37:20.100 align:middle line:84%
The bull market in gold
and silver, which is again,

00:37:20.100 --> 00:37:22.440 align:middle line:84%
it's really just a bear
market in currencies.

00:37:22.440 --> 00:37:24.610 align:middle line:84%
It's not like a
gold coin has gained

00:37:24.610 --> 00:37:26.830 align:middle line:90%
in value over the past 10 years.

00:37:26.830 --> 00:37:29.300 align:middle line:84%
It's the currencies that
it's being valued in.

00:37:29.300 --> 00:37:32.220 align:middle line:84%
Not just the dollar, the
euro, the rupee, yuan,

00:37:32.220 --> 00:37:34.030 align:middle line:90%
that's been going down in value.

00:37:34.030 --> 00:37:36.360 align:middle line:84%
And what's been causing it,
what's been causing people

00:37:36.360 --> 00:37:40.630 align:middle line:84%
to trade in those dollars
and euros for gold and silver

00:37:40.630 --> 00:37:42.154 align:middle line:90%
is not greed but fear.

00:37:42.154 --> 00:37:42.820 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:37:42.820 --> 00:37:46.940 align:middle line:84%
>>HOFFMAN: So when you buy
even land, or certainly

00:37:46.940 --> 00:37:48.520 align:middle line:84%
stocks and bonds,
you're buying it

00:37:48.520 --> 00:37:50.210 align:middle line:90%
because you want to gain value.

00:37:50.210 --> 00:37:52.657 align:middle line:84%
You want this thing
to grow in value.

00:37:52.657 --> 00:37:54.490 align:middle line:10%
Whereas with gold, you
buy it because you're

00:37:54.490 --> 00:37:57.924 align:middle line:10%
scared that everything else is
going to lose value against it.

00:37:57.924 --> 00:37:58.590 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:37:58.590 --> 00:38:00.990 align:middle line:10%
So let's take this
period of time.

00:38:00.990 --> 00:38:05.050 align:middle line:10%
And right now, we're talking
it's the beginning of August.

