they should be
quite a bit higher.

00:39:17.186 --> 00:39:19.380 align:middle line:84%
>>HOFFMAN: Yeah, but
staying at a record level,

00:39:19.380 --> 00:39:21.560 align:middle line:84%
considering that gold
hasn't gone anywhere,

00:39:21.560 --> 00:39:24.260 align:middle line:84%
the efforts that have
been made to keep it down

00:39:24.260 --> 00:39:26.570 align:middle line:84%
should tell you how strong
the underlying demand is.

00:39:26.570 --> 00:39:28.460 align:middle line:90%
Now that's only one part of it.

00:39:28.460 --> 00:39:32.720 align:middle line:84%
Again, the other Achilles
heel of these manipulators

00:39:32.720 --> 00:39:35.470 align:middle line:84%
is that gold is priced
in all currencies.

00:39:35.470 --> 00:39:38.960 align:middle line:84%
So it's one thing to try
to keep it down in dollars,

00:39:38.960 --> 00:39:40.802 align:middle line:84%
but there's only
300 million people

00:39:40.802 --> 00:39:42.260 align:middle line:84%
in the worl-- in
the United States.

00:39:42.260 --> 00:39:43.760 align:middle line:84%
And there's another
6 plus billion

00:39:43.760 --> 00:39:46.020 align:middle line:84%
around the world who
trade in other currencies.

00:39:46.020 --> 00:39:49.280 align:middle line:84%
Now the euro has been
collapsing against the dollar.

00:39:49.280 --> 00:39:49.980 align:middle line:90%
So guess what?

00:39:49.980 --> 00:39:51.920 align:middle line:84%
Euro gold is almost
at its all time high.

00:39:51.920 --> 00:39:53.519 align:middle line:84%
As we speak, it's
about 5% from it.

00:39:53.519 --> 00:39:54.810 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah, it makes sense.

00:39:54.810 --> 00:39:57.040 align:middle line:84%
>>HOFFMAN: Whereas, the
US price is 20% below.

00:39:57.040 --> 00:39:58.790 align:middle line:84%
So when I say
they're manipulating,

00:39:58.790 --> 00:40:00.250 align:middle line:90%
it's not just the US.

00:40:00.250 --> 00:40:02.140 align:middle line:84%
It could be people
from Greece alone,

00:40:02.140 --> 00:40:04.970 align:middle line:84%
and Spain, who blow
out this cartel,

00:40:04.970 --> 00:40:08.160 align:middle line:84%
because they all at once, you
know, the bank runs intensify,

00:40:08.160 --> 00:40:10.470 align:middle line:84%
and they say, we don't
want to be Spanish banks.

00:40:10.470 --> 00:40:12.340 align:middle line:90%
We want to be in real money.

00:40:12.340 --> 00:40:15.290 align:middle line:84%
And so the point is
it's like putting

00:40:15.290 --> 00:40:16.500 align:middle line:90%
the fingers in the dike.

00:40:16.500 --> 00:40:18.740 align:middle line:84%
There's just holes
popping up everywhere.

00:40:18.740 --> 00:40:22.390 align:middle line:84%
They can't-- for one, they can't
keep the physical price down.

00:40:22.390 --> 00:40:25.050 align:middle line:84%
Because when they push
the paper price too low,

00:40:25.050 --> 00:40:26.790 align:middle line:84%
everyone comes to
our firm and buys it.

00:40:26.790 --> 00:40:28.360 align:middle line:90%
That's when demand takes off.

00:40:28.360 --> 00:40:31.080 align:middle line:84%
And for two, if they try
to make it like, oh, they

00:40:31.080 --> 00:40:33.890 align:middle line:84%
want you to think because
the euro collapsing-- Europe

00:40:33.890 --> 00:40:35.720 align:middle line:90%
is collapsing, it's a deflation.

00:40:35.720 --> 00:40:38.430 align:middle line:84%
But the fact is when
the euro collapses,

00:40:38.430 --> 00:40:40.630 align:middle line:84%
people have
inflation over there.

00:40:40.630 --> 00:40:44.650 align:middle line:84%
They had record gasoline
prices in Europe this summer.

00:40:44.650 --> 00:40:46.100 align:middle line:90%
So people want to buy gold.

00:40:46.100 --> 00:40:48.340 align:middle line:84%
So again, it's
very, very difficult

00:40:48.340 --> 00:40:51.570 align:middle line:84%
for them to just to keep
it flat, like you said,

00:40:51.570 --> 00:40:53.270 align:middle line:84%
let alone to keep
it from exploding.

00:40:53.270 --> 00:40:55.240 align:middle line:84%
And yes, what I think
is going to happen,

00:40:55.240 --> 00:40:57.370 align:middle line:84%
I think it's going to
go to levels that people

00:40:57.370 --> 00:40:58.020 align:middle line:90%
can't imagine.

00:40:58.020 --> 00:41:00.860 align:middle line:84%
But again, there's a difference
between the real value

00:41:00.860 --> 00:41:02.310 align:middle line:90%
and the nominal value.

00:41:02.310 --> 00:41:05.690 align:middle line:84%
Because I can do the simple
math and say gold price

00:41:05.690 --> 00:41:08.760 align:middle line:84%
should be today $15,000
to $20,000 an ounce.

00:41:08.760 --> 00:41:09.260 align:middle line:90%
I mean--

