That's not like predicting
a stock will go up.

00:41:13.500 --> 00:41:15.950 align:middle line:84%
I'm saying this is how much
money the government tells you

00:41:15.950 --> 00:41:16.760 align:middle line:90%
they've printed.

00:41:16.760 --> 00:41:18.000 align:middle line:84%
Not that they've
actually printed.

00:41:18.000 --> 00:41:18.760 align:middle line:84%
It's what they tell
you they printed.

00:41:18.760 --> 00:41:20.930 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So with that ratio,
that should be what it's worth.

00:41:20.930 --> 00:41:21.240 align:middle line:90%
>>HOFFMAN: Yes.

00:41:21.240 --> 00:41:22.531 align:middle line:90%
That's what it should be today.

00:41:22.531 --> 00:41:24.840 align:middle line:84%
Of course, each minute
they print another dollar,

00:41:24.840 --> 00:41:26.350 align:middle line:90%
that price target goes up.

00:41:26.350 --> 00:41:29.390 align:middle line:84%
So at some point, I believe,
as all fiat currencies do,

00:41:29.390 --> 00:41:30.520 align:middle line:90%
the dollar will go.

00:41:30.520 --> 00:41:34.364 align:middle line:84%
And gold will become
infinite in current dollars

00:41:34.364 --> 00:41:35.280 align:middle line:90%
for what that's worth.

